HEADWORD: adulterated
<hw>adulterated</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>having been made
impure by addition of inferior ingredients; -- said of substances or
foods</def> <note> used ususally of articles of commerce, dulted with
less costly materials so as to enhance profit; -- usually imlying that
the dilution is surreptitious and unethical</note>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> adulterate, debased</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>adulterating</ent>⟦br⟧
